- Updated [micropolis_bridge.cpp](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/micropolis/micropolis_bridge.cpp:72) to:
  - allocate raw storage,
  - zero it before constructing `Micropolis`,
  - placement-new construct `Micropolis`,
  - and destroy via matching custom deleter.
- Why: `Micropolis` has pointer members (including map/history bases) that are not constructor-initialized before `initMapArrays()` is called. Zeroed pre-construction storage ensures those pointers start null, so map buffers are allocated correctly before `clearMap()` writes.

